* Upload structured (JSON) overall results with runner status to RaceRoster (LPT).
*   Param 1 (%1):  The RaceRoster sub-event ID.
*
*   Note:           LPT requires structured (JSON) results so RaceRoster can parse
*                   the data for Live Predictive Tracking. Unstructured (text) results
*                   are not supported by LPT.
*
*   Recommendation:
*     - Define sub-event IDs in Entries.INI (e.g. %rr_5k%) rather than hardcoding
*       them here or in multiple listings — one place to update when IDs change.
*     - Run @CalcStatus.lst before uploading so RUNNER STATUS is populated.

External Report To  RaceRoster
Records Per Page    100000
No Page Numbers
List DNF
Dq Field            DNF

Header
.INCLUDE            RACENAME
##%1##
.End of Header

Select              BIB
>                   0
And
Select              DNF
EQ
Field               BIB
Field               Name
Field               Sex
Field               AGE
Field               DIV
Field               City
Field               State
Field               DIVPLACE
Field               DIVTOTAL
Field               SEXPLACE
Field               SEXTOTAL
Field               RUNNER STATUS

Event               Finish
minus               GunStart
Time Format         H:MM:SS.01
Field Header        Gun Time

Event               Finish
minus               ChipStart
Time Format         H:MM:SS.01
Field Header        Chip Time

* LPT split: elapsed time from actual chip mat crossing to checkpoint (not gun time)
Event               LPTCheckpoint
minus               ChipStart
Time Format         H:MM:SS.01
Field Header        LPT Time
